Resolves the host-side claude runtime for billed (subscription-auth) cage launches: locates the real `claude` binary, locates the host's OAuth credential file, and synthesizes a minimal `~/.claude.json` written into the run directory so claude auto-detects the bound credential inside the cage without prompting for login or trust.

Auth model is deliberate and narrow: only `~/.claude/.credentials.json` is bound read-only into the cage — nothing else under `~/.claude` — and the synthesized `~/.claude.json` carries only the host's `oauthAccount` object plus onboarding/trust pre-completion fields, preserving blinding (no project history, no other credentials leak in). API calls still exit only through the host proxy relay at `CAGE_BASE_URL = "http://127.0.0.1:8080"` (`ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` points there), which passes through the `Authorization` header.

Key behavioral details an editor must preserve: `which_claude_realpath()` runs `readlink -f "$(command -v claude)"` via `sh -c` because Claude Code installs a `bin/claude` symlink to a versioned ELF under `share/` — resolving through `command -v` alone isn't enough. `synth_claude_config`'s `projects` map key must be `target_root`'s exact host path (the real workspace path per ADR-046, no fixed alias) because that's the key claude's own trust map uses internally; a mismatch makes the trust dialog reappear and breaks headless operation. `random_anonymous_id` reads raw bytes from `/dev/urandom` directly (no `rand` crate dependency) since cryptographic strength isn't required, only per-run freshness for telemetry.

Entry point: `resolve_claude_runtime(rundir: &Path, target_root: &Path) -> Result<ClaudeRuntime, CageError>`, returning `ClaudeRuntime { claude_binary, credentials, claude_config_json }`. Errors are `CageError::Protocol` for missing `claude` on `PATH`, unset `HOME`, or missing credentials file (with a message suggesting the operator log in via Claude Code once on the host); `CageError::Io`/`CageError::Json` propagate from config read/parse/write. Invariant: never panics on missing host files — all missing-path cases return typed `Protocol` errors instead.